  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "**What happened**:\r\nWhen a pod that uses a CSI raw block volume is deleted, kubelet leaves some files in /var/lib/kubelet, without cleaning them.\r\n\r\n```\r\n/var/lib/kubelet/plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/volumeDevices/pvc-68ddc376-0d7d-4187-9911-c585cc6c8628/data/vol_data.json\r\n/var/lib/kubelet/plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/volumeDevices/publish/pvc-68ddc376-0d7d-4187-9911-c585cc6c8628 (empty directory)\r\n```\r\n\r\n(where `pvc-68ddc376-0d7d-4187-9911-c585cc6c8628` is name of a PV used as a raw block volume.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nAll files are cleaned up, only `/var/lib/kubelet/plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/volumeDevices/staging` and `/var/lib/kubelet/plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/volumeDevices/publish` remain, as they can contain files / directories of other raw block volumes.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nRun hostpath tests and check /var/lib/kubelet after the tests.\r\n\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): last week master, 641321c94c3e0943a57230596164e2e8f2eb2c52\r\n\r\n/sig storage",
